******
[2]
Date: Thu 6 Nov 2008
Source: UPI.com [edited]
<http://www.upi.com/Odd_News/2008/11/06/Woman_ran_with_rabid_fox_on_arm/UPI-72431226017114/>


A Chino Valley, Arizona, woman said she is receiving a series of shots
after she ran 1.5 miles (2.4 km) with a rabid fox hanging from her arm. The
30 year old woman said she encountered the fox while she was jogging in the
late afternoon Monday [3 May 2008] at the base of Granite Mountain, The
(Prescott, Arizona) Courier reported on Thursday [6 Nov 2008]. "I knew
something was wrong when its eyes locked in on me," the woman said. She
said the fox bit her foot before she grabbed it by the neck. "As soon as I
grabbed its neck, it started thrashing and grabbed my left arm," she said.
She said the rabid animal clamped down on her arm so hard that she had to
run the mile and a half back to her car with the fox in tow. She said she
managed to pry the fox's jaws open and throw it in her trunk before driving
to the hospital.

Dwight D'Evelyn, spokesman for the Yavapai County Sheriff's Office, said
the fox also bit a Yavapai County animal control officer who was trying to
retrieve the animal from the trunk of the car. D'Evelyn said the bitten
woman will require 5 rabies shots during the next few weeks, while the
animal control officer will only need 2 or 3 due to a pre-exposure rabies
vaccination.

