[Apart from recording the added hazard of exposure to rabies virus
infection as a consequence of jogging, church going, and living on the
outskirts of towns, the most significant observation is that most
terrestrial animals in Arizona that were found to have rabies had been
exposed to a variant of rabies virus carried by bats.

The states of Arizona and South Carolina can be located using the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the USA at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=40,-97.6,4>. The location of Chino valley,
Arizona, can be found at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chino_Valley,_Arizona>, and the location of
Spartanburg County, South Carolina at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spartanburg_County,_South_Carolina>. - Mod.CP]
